results.reasoning_alignment: This is literally a charitable fundraising platform where federal employees donate to their favorite charities. Hawaii FIDO could be listed as a CFC charity, giving access to all federal employees in Hawaii (military, government workers).

results.reasoning_impact: Access to all federal employees and retirees through workplace giving. Hawaii has a massive federal/military workforce. One CFC listing = ongoing annual donations from potentially thousands of federal workers. Enormous multiplier effect.
results.outreach_strategy: High-priority prospect. Apply to become a listed CFC charity through givecfc.org. Hawaii has a massive federal and military workforce (Joint Base Pearl Harbor-Hickam, federal agencies). Being listed in the CFC means federal employees can make automatic payroll deductions to Hawaii FIDO. This is an ongoing annual revenue stream, not a one-time donation. Follow the CFC charity application process and ensure Hawaii FIDO meets eligibility requirements.
